@page "/docs/4.3/components/alerts"

<DocHead Title="Alerts" RelatedBootstrapDoc="4.3/components/alerts/">
    Provide contextual feedback messages for typical user actions with the handful of available and flexible alert messages.
</DocHead>

<h2 id="examples">Examples</h2>
<p>Alerts are available for any length of text, as well as an optional dismiss button. For proper styling, use one of the eight <strong>required</strong> contextual options (e.g., <code class="highlighter-rouge">success</code>). For inline dismissal, set the <a href="#dismissing">Dismissable</a> parameter.</p>

<Example File=@typeof(AlertsExample1) />

<AssistiveTechCallout />

<h3 id="link-color">Link color</h3>

<p>By importing the overrides to the standard HTML components in Bootstrap.NET with <code class="highlighter-rouge">&#64;using Egil.RazorComponents.Bootstrap.Components.Html</code>, the <code class="highlighter-rouge">.alert-link</code> utility class is automatically applied to links placed inside any alerts to quickly provide matching colored links within any alert.</p>

<Example File=@typeof(AlertsLinkColor) />

<h3 id="additional-content">Additional content</h3>

<p>Alerts can also contain additional HTML elements like headings, paragraphs and dividers.</p>
<p>By importing the overrides to the standard HTML components in Bootstrap.NET with <code class="highlighter-rouge">&#64;using Egil.RazorComponents.Bootstrap.Components.Html</code>, headings will automatically have the <code class="highlighter-rouge">.alert-heading</code> utility class is automatically applied to quickly provide matching colored headlines within any alert.</p>

<Example File=@typeof(AlertsAdditionalContent) />

<h3 id="dismissing">Dismissing</h3>
<p>To make an alert dismissable by the users, you only need to set the property <code class="highlighter-rouge">Dismissable="true"</code> on the Alert component.</p>
